      • setLabel

        public void setLabel(String text)
        Sets the label for a relationship cardinality. Processes the raw text inputted by the user to a correct cardinality label text in the format "..". If the user typed in rubbish, the cardinalities won't be changed. Instead of two dots, the user can type in an arbitrary number of dots or even '-'.
        Specified by:
        setLabel in interface RelationLabel
        Parameters:
        text - The raw cardinality string.
        See Also:
        RelationLabel.getLabel()
